<p>You have entered... </p>
<p>Name: {{model.firstName}} {{model.lastName}}</p>
<p>Email: {{model.email}}</p>
<p>Twitter: {{model.twitter}}</p>
{{!-- The {{action}} helper is one of the most useful features in Ember. It allows us to bind an action in
the template to an action in the templateâ€™s Controller or Route. 
By default it is bound to the click
action, but it can be bound to other actions. --}}


<form {{action "save" on="submit"}}>
	<h2 class="error">{{errorMessage}}</h2>
	<fieldset>
		{{input value=model.firstName placeholder="First Name"}}<br>
		{{input value=model.lastName placeholder="Last Name"}}<br>
		{{input value=model.email placeholder="email"}}<br>
		{{input value=model.twitter placeholder="twitter"}}<br>
		{{!--Ember expects us to define our action handlers inside the property actions in the Controller or
			Route. --}}
		<input type="submit" value="Save" class="primary">
		<button {{action "cancel"}}>Cancel</button>
	</fieldset>
</form>